⚠️ Current Behavior Notes
Deduplication Logic: Uses _ingested_at timestamp to keep latest. Assumes newer = better. If source data has its own event timestamps, consider using those instead.

Null Handling:

Key fields (countries) → Records filtered out
Flight counts → Coalesced to 0
Question: Is 0 the right default? Consider business rules.
SCD Type 1 (No History): Old values are overwritten. If you need to track how flight counts change over time, consider:

SCD Type 2 (keep historical versions)
Change Data Feed (enabled, but not consumed downstream)
Partition Pruning: Uses today's partition only. If you re-process historical data, you'll need to pass specific partition_dt values.

